snippet: New York is signing up enough young subscribers to make the insurance system viable, state senators were told at a hearing, but some enrollees have found problems in the program.
abstract: New York State Senate hearing shows that state is enrolling a significant number of young subscribers on its health insurance exchange, but many of those already enrolled have raised questions about rules that limit which doctors they can see, or are having problems finding out if their doctors are covered.
